cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper is about object detection using reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves using a hierarchical tree-like representation of region candidates, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of reinforcement learning to train the agent also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves making decisions at each step to refine the bounding box, which is a task commonly associated with robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes different reward functions to guide the agent, which is a topic in control theory (cs.CR).
